rawContent:
Hidden In Plain Sight.

Have We Just Uncovered the Hidden North Pole?

In the North Pole, many ancient maps depicted 4 continents that were divided by rivers, in a cross shape, with a black magnetic mountain called Rupes Nigra located in their center. The Rupes Nigra ("Black Rock"), a phantom island,  was believed to be a 33-mile-wide black rock Mercator, a 16th-century cartographer (who's map is below) actually  describes the rock's circumference as 33 "French" miles) located at the Magnetic North Pole or at the North Pole itself.  Is this why all compasses point dead North?  The North Star (Polaris) is also directly above this point.

What is even more interesting, is if you super impose the Mercator Map with today's Google Earth image of the North Pole there are some striking similarities.

Many cultures believe the Garden of Eden, with the Tree of Life is located there also, under the North Star.  It's beginning to sound a lot like Christmas, that we worship each year.

We are now told, like we tell our children, that Santa (an anagram for Satan) lives there.  Why did they pick that location to perpetuate the myth of Santa?  probably because we now think it is all fake and pay no attention to it, like it is just fantasy and we just cant get there.  

The Mercator Map is not properly skewed (see Asia) to fit onto Googles Ball, nor am I saying this is definitely the North Pole lands, but look how similar the maps are. And why does Google’s Map have dark blue shading over where the North Pole continents would be as seen on Mercator's Map? 

What do you think? Research #flatearth
